  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_0\"\u003e\n\n                    \u003ch3\u003eSummary\u003c/h3\u003e\n        \n            \u003cdiv\u003e    \u003cul\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Google may start reminding Pixel users to enable Wi-Fi calling in weak signal areas.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        The reminder will allow users to enable Wi-Fi calling automatically or dismiss the prompt.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        This intel comes from an APK teardown and the feature may not come to fruition.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n    \n        \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDid you know a mobile network isn\u0026#39;t the only way to make phone calls? You can also phone a friend via Wi-Fi. This is particularly helpful in areas with weak or no mobile network coverage, especially as we wait for satellite connections to become more widely available. \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/disable-wifi-calling-tutorial/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eWi-Fi calling\u003c/a\u003e exists, but it\u0026#39;s usually a feature that you need to enable on your phone. And, unless your phone automatically does it for you, you might not remember to enable it in times of need.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"e8be-4503-a5b78e7cabe8\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https: